Unconstitutional. The IRS cannot override the 2nd Amendment.
Yes and no.  The Executive branch has the right to regulate.  This just feeds into their modus operandi.  They'll inundate the legal system with regulations that makes it near impossible to own a firearm legally.  They can't make a law that explicitly outlaws firearm ownership, but they *CAN* make a series of laws that effectively accomplish just that.

Think of it like dieing from 1000 tiny cuts instead of one massive laceration.
